The Banking Management System is a console-based Java application that simulates core banking operations such as user registration, account creation, money transactions, and balance inquiry.
The system is built using Java, JDBC, and MySQL, ensuring secure and reliable database-driven operations.
This project demonstrates real-world banking workflows, transaction handling, and database consistency using JDBC transactions.

Key Features:

